The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         BRIEFS
                  
	Siliguri, Oct. 19: The hills and the Dooars are bracing for a spell of strikes in the peak tourist season  called by outfits opposing the demand for Gorkhaland.     
	The Bangla Bangla Bhasha Banchao Committee has called a 24-hour north Bengal bandh on Wednesday. Citus inde-finite transport strike will also begin that day. The Shiv Sena has called a 48-hour bandh in Siliguri subdivision, parts of Jalpaiguri and the Dooars from Tuesday.        
	Midnapore: The IIT Kharagpur student held on Saturday on the charge of selling drugs has been remanded in 14 days jail custody. About 100gm of heroin was found on Preyankar Biswas of the agriculture and food engineering department. Sanjoy De, 25, and Ishque Mohammad, 35, who were found in his room, have been charged with peddling. Kharag- pur resident Sanjoy was held earlier for allegedly stealing a laptop from the IIT. Police said Ishque, from Murshidabad, had brought the drugs.                                                                                                                                                                   
